g analyst he held positions in manufacturing sales marketing product development and finance during the  fordunited auto workers labor talks which launched the employee involvement movement that revolutionized the industry he served on the company’s national bargaining team in  he began a month course of study as an alfred p sloan fellow at the massachusetts institute of technology he was elected chairman and managing director of ford switzerland in  as head of business strategy for the ford automotive group in  he helped develop guidelines for establishing lowvolume manufacturing plants in emerging markets after being appointed general manager of climate control division in  he led a profit turnaround and a major improvement in product quality he also established the company’s first wildlife habitat at a plant location and the first automotive plant in the world to use  percent postconsumer materials in all of its plastic parts while he was general manager the division won the president’s commission on environmental quality award bill ford was elected a company vice president and head of the company’s commercial truck vehicle center in  he left that position in order to assume the chairmanship of the board of directors’ finance committee in  in addition to his duties as chairman he served as chief executive officer of the company from october  to september  when he was named executive chairman as ceo he improved quality lowered costs and delivered exciting new products during his time in that position he took the company from a  billion loss in  to three straight years of profitability a lifelong environmentalist bill ford is committed to developing products that benefit customers and society under his leadership in  ford motor company published its first corporate citizenship report outlining the economic environmental and social impact of company products and operations around the world in  the company completed the world’s largest brownfield reclamation project the restoration of its ford rouge center in metropolitan detroit he also championed the escape hybrid the world’s first hybridelectric sport utility vehicle “during the last industry downturn ford invested heavily in fuel economy and technology at a time when many others were pulling back” he says “it absolutely was the right thing to do” looking to the future in  he began outlining the company’s vision of what sustainable transportation will look like in the years ahead as well as the steps it will take to get there that future includes vehicles that communicate with each other and the world around them to make driving safer ease traffic congestion and sustain the environment as the next step in these efforts in  the company announced ford smart mobility its plan to deliver advances in connectivity mobility autonomous vehicles the customer experience and data and analytics “my greatgrandfather helped put the world on wheels so everyone could enjoy the benefits of mobility” he says “our vision is to expand on that thinking using advanced technology and new business models so that personal mobility remains viable in a crowded world” bill ford’s charitable volunteer and business efforts are highlighted by his commitment to the city of detroit as vice chairman of the detroit lions professional football team he led efforts to build a new environmentallyfriendly stadium in detroit that was the site of super bowl xl through detroit lions charities he helped develop the detroit police athletic league youth football program into one of the largest in the country under his leadership the company’s philanthropic arm ford motor company fund and community services focused its efforts on helping communities supporting education and improving safety through driving skills training in  he launched the ford volunteer corps to enhance the efforts of employee volunteers serving communities around the world in its first ten years ford  volunteers worked on more than  projects in  countries in  he championed the  under thirty program to develop the next generation of ford philanthropic leaders and the bill ford better world challenge which provides grant funding for projects that engage employees and local nonprofits in addressing needs that will improve community life and make people’s lives better bill ford is chairman of the board of the detroit economic club a member of the board of trustees of the henry ford and the henry ford health system and is chairman of the new michigan initiative of business leaders for michigan he also served on the board of directors of ebay inc from  to  he was inducted into the irish america hall of fame in  he also is a founding partner of fontinalis partners llc a michiganbased investment firm that acts as a strategic operating partner to transportation infrastructure technology companies  in recognition of his commitment to education and devotion to the detroit community in  he was given the ambassador for humanity award by the usc shoah foundation institute bill ford was born in detroit in may  he is an avid fly fisherman and car enthusiast enjoys playing hockey and tennis and is a martial arts black belt he holds a bachelor of arts degree from princeton university and a master of science degree in management from massachusetts institute of technology mit he also has been awarded an honorary doctor of environmental sciences and engineering degree from koc university an honorary doctor of laws degree from the university of michigan an honorary doctor of humane letters degree from bradley university and an honorary doctorate of economic science from university college cork and the national university of ireland close select a location current location united states  english region country language longtime lehigh county judge stepping down  the morning call photos agents organize exclusive showing of seven luxury lehigh valley homes severe weather alert in philadelphia northampton monroe lehigh delaware carbon and berks countiesjuly  news breaking news lehigh county judge william e ford stepping down contributed photo  the morning call judge william e ford ed note local judge william e ford ed note local contributed photo  the morning call laurie mason schroedercontact reporterof the morning call longtime lehigh county judge stepping down after  years of hoisting a gavel lehigh county judge william e ford has decided to step down from the benchthe yearold allentown republican will leave his post at the end of the year to open his own law firm in center city focusing on civil litigation mediation and estate lawits been wonderful ford said but i feel that im ready for a new challenge as a judge i see all areas of the law when i see an area that i havent practiced or see a lawyer coming up with a new solution to a problem i think why havent i tried that before i think it will be intellectually stimulatingford said hes also motivated by all the growth in downtown allentown and believes theres room for more attorneys there its all very exciting and i want to be a part of it he saidduring his tenure ford worked in all four divisions of the court — civil criminal family and orphans court he currently oversees criminal court and adoption hearingsford was elected in  and retained for year terms in  and  he submitted his resignation to gov tom wolf on monday and is leaving four years into his current termfords departure will leave a vacancy on the bench that can only be filled by gubernatorial appointment since it comes too late for a special election the states current budget impasse makes an appointment unlikely said kerry r turtzo the countys deputy district court administrator weve heard throughout the state that its just not happening he saidfords announcement coincides with senior judge lawrence j brenners exit brenner must step down because hes reached the mandatory senior judge retirement age of  turtzo saidturtzo said other judges will take over fords caseload and a senior jurist from philadelphia judge john l braxton has committed to spending one week each month in lehigh to hear casesits going to be lean turtzo saidford said hes going to miss wearing the black robe being a judge was satisfying he said especially when he had the opportunity to help someone who came before himjudges are in a position to correct things and to right a wrong when that happens its very rewarding he saidford said he hopes to emulate the attorneys hes observed from the bench who are caring championsworking with lawyers who truly care about their clients has been a highlight of my career he said a caring attitude really helps achieve the best result in a casehe said hell miss the courthouse staff which he called the most professional in the regiona graduate of desales university ford received his law degree from the dickinson school of law in  he has lectured at desales muhlenberg and chestnut hill collegesford served as a captain in the judge advocate generals corps of the marine reserve from  to  he was a county prosecutor from  to he is a former basketball coach for the catholic youth organization and former baseball coach for the west end youth association and has been involved in numerous other civic organizations and charitiesford and his wife rosemary have  children who range in age from  to  years old he said the family is very excited about his next career moveeveryone has offered to help were all very energized he saidlmasonmcallcomtwitter lehighcourts privacy policy copyright   the morning call  found dead in sweltering truck in immigrantsmuggling attempt in texas kushner to face both intelligence committees this week questions swirl about livein adult advisers role in piazza death breakingsportsobitsbiz cyclearts  entenewspaperclassifiedsinsider guide° ford – new cars trucks suvs crossovers  hybrids  vehicles built just for you‎  fordcom search anytime by typing popular on fordcom focus fiesta mustang f how do i pay my bill update my sync replace